{%- liquid
  assign afq_title = title | default: 'Frequently Asked Questions — Attars'
  assign afq_intro = intro | default: 'Everything you need to know about attars, usage, longevity, and care.'
  assign afq_product_title = product.title | default: 'this attar'
  assign afq_q_apply = 'How do I apply ' | append: afq_product_title | append: ' for best results?'
-%}

<section class="afq" aria-label="Attar FAQs">
  <div class="afq__inner">
    <p class="afq__eyebrow">ATTAR GUIDE</p>
    <h2 class="afq__title">{{ afq_title }}</h2>
    <p class="afq__intro">{{ afq_intro }}</p>

    <div class="afq__list">
      <details class="afq__item" open>
        <summary class="afq__q">What is an attar, and how is it different from perfume?</summary>
        <p class="afq__a">Attar is a concentrated, alcohol-free fragrance oil traditionally distilled from natural botanicals. It usually feels richer and more intimate on skin compared to alcohol-based sprays.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="afq__item">
        <summary class="afq__q">How do I apply {{ afq_product_title }} for best results?</summary>
        <p class="afq__a">Apply 1-2 small dabs on pulse points like wrists, neck, and behind ears. For a softer trail, apply on inner elbows or on fabric edges after patch testing.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="afq__item">
        <summary class="afq__q">How long does attar last on skin?</summary>
        <p class="afq__a">Most attars last 6-10 hours depending on skin type, weather, and application amount. On moisturized skin, longevity is usually better.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="afq__item">
        <summary class="afq__q">Can I layer attars with other fragrances?</summary>
        <p class="afq__a">Yes. Start with lighter floral/citrus attars first, then add deeper woody or resinous notes. Keep dosage minimal to avoid overpowering blends.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="afq__item">
        <summary class="afq__q">Is attar suitable for daily use?</summary>
        <p class="afq__a">Absolutely. Attars are ideal for daily wear, rituals, meditation, and office-friendly scenting when applied in small amounts.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="afq__item">
        <summary class="afq__q">How should I store attars?</summary>
        <p class="afq__a">Keep bottles tightly closed, away from direct sunlight, heat, and humidity. Store upright in a cool, dark place to preserve aroma quality.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{%- if product != blank -%}
